      <div class="box ans col">
        <p><i class="icon fa-solid fa-arrow-right fa-1x"></i>
          Image Encryption is a technique in which we will encrypt an image with the help of a key in order to prevent any misuse of it. Here, the key plays a vital role as we will use it for both encryption and decryption. So, if one tries to encrypt an image using the following steps, the security of the key must be ensured first.
         </p>
      </div>
    </div>


    <div class="row">
      <div class="box steps col">
        <h2 class="box"><i class="icon fa-solid fa-hashtag fa-l"></i> Steps </h5>
        <ol>
          <li>Open Image file and read it.</li>
          <li> Convert image into bytearray.</li>
          <li>Now use the key and perform XOR with every element of the bytearray.</li>
          <li>After perfoming the XOR operation, the bytearray thus now becomes encrypted and write it in the decrypted image file.</li>
          <li> For decryption, use the same process but now the decrypted image is the file on which we will perform the operation</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
   
    

    <div class="box code_text">
    <pre>
      <code class="language-python">
        <div>
          file=open('decrypted.jpg','rb')
          original=file.read()
          file.close()
          
          
          original=bytearray(original)
          key=48
          
          for i,j in enumerate(original):
              original[i]= j^key
          
          file=open('decrypted.jpg','wb')
          file.write(original)
          file.close()

        </div>
      </code>
